\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 178. S. sericea }All., {\i Fl. Pedem.}{\b  2}: 81 (1785). Stems up to 50 cm, pubescent, ascending, branched. Leaves linear-lanceolate. Flowers solitary and terminal at ends of stems, rarely 2 or 3 in a reduced monochasial cyme. Calyx 12-20(-23) mm; teeth lanceolate, acute or subobtuse. Petals pink. Carpophore 4-10(-12) mm. Seeds 1-1·4 mm, reniform or elongate-reniform, dark brown; faces concave-excavate, striate; back grooved between rounded or angled (not winged and undulate) sides. 2n = 24.{\i  Maritime sands. •? W. Mediterranean region.} Bl Co ?Ga It Sa.
