\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 183. S. cerastoides }L.,{\i  Sp. Pl}. 417 (1753). Whole plant somewhat hispid, glandular-viscid above; stems up to 25 cm, often branched at base. Flowers in lax, raceme-like monochasial cymes; pedicels not longer than calyx. Calyx 8-11 mm, cylindrical-clavate, glandular-pubescent, becoming very strongly contracted both above and below capsule in fruit, toothed for 1/3 of its length with lanceolate, acute teeth; veins conspicuously anastomosing. Petal-limb small, bifid, pink. Capsule 6-8 mm, shortly attenuate above; carpophore 2-4 mm. Seeds dark brown; faces deeply concave, striate; back wide with narrow, shallow central groove. 2n = 24.{\i  S. & E. Spain, S. Portugal, Islas Baleares; a few localities in the E. Mediterranean.} Bl Cr Gr Hs Ju Lu.
