\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 184. S. tridentata }Desf., {\i Fl. Atl. }{\b 1}: 349 (1798). Whole plant hispidulous; stems 10-40 cm, simple or branched. Flowers subsessile, in lax, raceme-like monochasial cymes. Calyx 11-14 mm, ellipsoid-cylindrical, becoming ovoid in fruit, not so strongly contracted as in {\b 183}, toothed to c. half-way, with acuminate or linear teeth; veins anastomosing. Petal-limb bifid, almost included in calyx, pink. Capsule 7-10 mm, attenuate above; carpophore 1-2 mm. Seeds dark brown; faces concave, striate; back wide, with wide, shallow central groove. 2n = 24.{\i  C., S. & E. Spain.} Hs.
