\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 186. S. colorata }Poiret,{\i  Voy. Barb.}{\b  2}: 163 (1789). Whole plant pubescent or puberulent. Stems 10-50 cm, decumbent to erect, branched. Leaves linear to ovate-spathulate. Pedicels shorter than calyx; bracts of a pair usually unequal. Calyx 11-13(-17) mm, cylindrical, becoming broadly clavate in fruit; teeth ovate, obtuse, densely ciliate. Petal-limb 5-9 mm, pink or white. Capsule 7-9 mm, ovoid; carpophore 5-7 mm. Seeds 1-1·5 mm, dark chestnut-brown. 2n = 24.{\i  S. Europe.} Al *Co Cr Gr Hs It Lu Sa Si Tu.
